---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/seo/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const TOS_VERSION = 'v2.0';
const TOS_LAST_UPDATED = '6 June 2026';
---

<PageLayout
  seo={{
    title: 'Terms of Service',
    description: 'PoopCheck Terms of Service. The rules for using the PoopCheck app and website.',
  }}
>
  <div class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
      <div class="mb-8">
        <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Terms of Service', href: '/terms/' }]} />
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-10">Version {TOS_VERSION} · Last updated: {TOS_LAST_UPDATED}</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none
        prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-[var(--color-text)]
        prose-h2:text-xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4
        prose-p:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] prose-p:leading-relaxed
        prose-strong:text-[var(--color-text)]
        prose-a:text-[var(--color-accent)]
      ">
        <h2>1. About these Terms</h2>
        <p>PoopCheck is operated by Soft All Things LLC (&quot;PoopCheck&quot;, &quot;we&quot;, &quot;us&quot;), a company registered in Wyoming, USA. These Terms are the agreement between you and us for using the PoopCheck app and website. By creating an account or using PoopCheck, you agree to them. If you do not agree, please do not use PoopCheck.</p>
        <h2>2. What PoopCheck is — and isn&#x27;t</h2>
        <p>PoopCheck is a wellness tracker: you scan your stool, record symptoms and lifestyle, and get AI-generated feedback to follow over time. It is not a medical device and does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. The feedback is informational only and can be wrong — always consult a qualified healthcare professional for any medical concern, and never rely on PoopCheck in an emergency.</p>
        <h2>3. Your account</h2>
        <p>You are responsible for keeping your login secure and for activity on your account, and for giving us accurate information. You can delete your account at any time in Settings, which deletes your personal data as described in the Privacy Notice.</p>
        <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
        <p>Use PoopCheck only for its intended purpose. Do not break the law; upload images that are not yours or that involve minors; harass others; hack, scrape, reverse-engineer, or overload the service; or use it to build a competing product or train a competing model. We may suspend or close accounts that break these rules.</p>
        <h2>5. Your content and how your data is used</h2>
        <p>You keep all rights in the content you submit — we do not own it — and you grant us a limited licence to host and process it so the app can work. Using PoopCheck requires you to accept how your data is used: analysing and storing your scans, training and improving PoopCheck&#x27;s own AI, and producing, licensing, and selling de-identified insights and datasets to third parties (such as researchers, AI developers, and health and wellness brands). If you do not accept this, or you later withdraw it, PoopCheck cannot analyse your scans and the app will not work for you. Two uses are separate and optional, and refusing them does not affect the app: selling raw, identifiable images to named buyers, and marketing emails. Full detail is in the Privacy Notice.</p>
        <h2>6. Premium and billing</h2>
        <p>PoopCheck&#x27;s core features are free. Premium is an optional paid subscription sold through the Apple App Store or Google Play. Subscriptions auto-renew until you cancel in your store account, and refunds are handled by the store under its rules.</p>
        <h2>7. Disclaimers and liability</h2>
        <p>PoopCheck is provided &quot;as is&quot;, without warranties, and is not a substitute for professional medical advice. To the extent the law allows, we are not liable for indirect or consequential damages, and our total liability is limited to the greater of what you paid us in the last 12 months or USD 100. Nothing here limits rights you cannot waive, including mandatory consumer rights in your country.</p>
        <h2>8. Changes, termination, and contact</h2>
        <p>We may update these Terms; for material changes we will give notice and ask you to accept the new version. We may suspend or close your account if you breach these Terms or as required by law. These Terms are governed by the laws of Wyoming, USA, without affecting the consumer protections you have where you live. Questions? Email poopcheck@softallthings.com.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
